Class ExpJobService

  • java.lang.Object
    • android.content.Context
      • android.content.ContextWrapper

            • com.example.foodtracker3.ExpJobService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.content.ComponentCallbacks, android.content.ComponentCallbacks2

    public class ExpJobService
extends android.app.job.JobService
    Class creates a job to run in the backgroung as a background service. It will check all the expiration dates of each products in the database and push notifications out depending on the expiration date
    Version:
    1.0.0 Jun 7, 2020
    Author:
    Marco Villafana

      • expDateChecker

        public void expDateChecker(java.util.ArrayList<Product> pList)
        Method will check each expiration_date of each product in the arraylist and determine if it is expired, with in 4 days of expiration, or not expired. If expired, it will send a notification on notification channel 1 using the sendOnChannel1 method. If not expired or with in 4 days of expiration it will send a notification on notification channel 2 using the sendOnChannel2 method.
        Parameters:
        pList - arraylist of all the products in the database.

      • sendOnChannel1

        public void sendOnChannel1(Product currProduct)
        Method creates a customized notification and notification group for expired products. Defines a action (navigating to the application home screen) to perform when notification is clicked on.
        Parameters:
        currProduct - the current Product object that has a expiration date that is expired or is about to expire
